-- Gazit-Globe Unit Buys Canadian Center for $70 Million
-- Tal Barak
-- 2007-03-15T16:14:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2007-03-15/gazit-globe-unit-buys-canadian-center-for-70-million-update1-.html

          
          
             Gazit-Globe Ltd. (GLOB) , Israel's second-
largest property developer by market value, said its Canadian
unit agreed to buy an Alberta shopping center for $70 million.  
 First Capital Realty Inc. (FCR)  will buy the Westmount Shopping
Center, in Edmonton, for cash and may invest another $20
million develop and renovate the asset, Tel Aviv-based Gazit
said in a statement to the stock exchange today.  
 ``Edmonton remains one of the country's strongest-growing
urban markets, and I believe we will continue to expand our
presence in the region,'' Brian Kozak, vice president of First
Capital Western Canada, said in the statement.  
 Shares of Gazit Globe fell 0.93 shekel, or 1.8 percent, to
51.74 shekels in  Tel Aviv .  
